{"title_page": "Bhavin Turakhia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Bhavin Turakhia\n| image = Bhavin Turakhia.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Bhavin Turakhia\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1979|12|21|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Bombay]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| nationality = \n| alma_mater = Arya Vidya Mandir<br>[[D. G. Ruparel College of Arts, Science and Commerce]]<br>[[Sydenham College of Commerce and Economics]]\n| occupation = {{unbulleted list| CEO & founder of Directi, [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]], Radix and [[Ringo (software)|Ringo]] | Co-founder of Zeta }}\n| known_for   = Directi, Radix, [[Ringo (software)|Ringo]], [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]], [[Zeta India|Zeta]], and [[CodeChef]]\n| website = \n| footnotes = \n| networth = {{increase}}[[United States dollar|US$]]1.3 [[1,000,000,000 (number)|billion]] (2016)<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/profile/bhavin-divyank-turakhia/ Bhavin Turakhia Profile]. [[Forbes.com]]. Retrieved 9 October 2016.</ref>\n| relations = \n}}\n\n'''Bhavin Turakhia''' (born 21 December 1979)  is an Indian billionaire <ref>{{cite news |title=Family matters: Bhavin Turakhia credits his father, humble beginnings for success |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/family-matters-bhavin-turakhia-credits-his-father-humble-beginnings-for-success/articleshow/72341438.cms |publisher=The Economic Times |date=Dec 3, 2019}}</ref> and serial entrepreneur<ref>{{cite news |title=Video I followed my father's advice and became a billionaire |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/business-50268357/i-followed-my-father-s-advice-and-became-a-billionaire |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=6 November 2019}}</ref>, and the founder of [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]], Radix, [[CodeChef]] and [[Zeta India|Zeta]]. He is the CEO of Flock and Zeta.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bhavin Turakhia to invest $25 mn in Flock, an enterprise team messenger|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/bhavin-turakhia-to-invest-25-mn-in-flock-an-enterprise-team-messenger/article9587411.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu Business Line]]|date=15 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"AsianAge\">{{cite news|last1=Banerjee|first1=Sudeshna|title=The winner takes it all|url=http://www.asianage.com/people/winner-takes-it-all-181|publisher=[[Asian Age]]|date=4 November 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ET\">{{cite news|last1=Mendonca|first1=Jochelle|title=Directi, founded by brothers Bhavin and Divyank Turakhia, to buy 1 lakh sq feet building|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/directi-founded-by-brothers-bhavin-and-divyank-turakhia-to-buy-1-lakh-sq-feet-building/articleshow/54287458.cms|publisher=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]|date=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0926\u094b \u092d\u093e\u0907\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u0902\u092a\u0928\u0940, 25000 \u0938\u0947 \u0936\u0941\u0930\u0941 \u0915\u0940 \u0914\u0930 6000 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091a\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0947\u091a \u0926\u0940|url=http://www.livehindustan.com/news/business/article1-divyank-turakhia-sold-medianet-for-chinese-company--554287.html|publisher=Live Hindutan|date=27 August 2017|location=New Delhi|language=Hindi}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=These Stories Of Overnight Success Defy Logic|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/12/29/these-stories-of-overnight-success-defy-logic/|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|date=2 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=John|first1=Jesus|title=Making life less taxing for staff and employers|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/specials/emerging-entrepreneurs/making-life-less-taxing-for-staff-and-employers/article8897928.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu Business Line]]|date=25 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Das|first1=Poulomi|title=This Indian tech company has one of the most fun hiring processes ever|url=http://www.businessinsider.in/This-Indian-tech-company-has-one-of-the-most-fun-hiring-processes-ever/articleshow/53544416.cms|publisher=[[Business Insider]]|date=4 August 2016}}</ref> In 2016, Bhavin was ranked as the 95th richest person in India, with a net worth of US$1.3 billion, along with his brother [[Divyank Turakhia]], according to ''[[Forbes]]''.<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news|last1=Raghunathan|first1=Anuradha|title=Meet the technology whiz kids Bhavin and Divyank Turakhia|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/india-rich-list-2016/meet-the-technology-whiz-kids-bhavin-and-divyank-turakhia/44959/1|newspaper=[[Forbes India]]|date=1 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Rajiv|title=Bootstrapping \u2013 running a startup without equity funding is the better way forward|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/bootstrapping-running-a-startup-without-equity-funding-is-the-better-way-forward/articleshow/50605934.cms|publisher=[[The Economic Times]]|date=18 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0907\u0938 \u0917\u0941\u091c\u0930\u093e\u0924\u0940 \u0928\u0947 18 \u0938\u093e\u0932 \u0915\u0940 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0939\u0940 \u0915\u0930 \u0932\u0940 8700 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u092e\u093e\u0908|url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/GUJ-AHM-OMC-the-success-story-of-two-brother-bhavin-turakhia-and-divyank-turakhia-news-hindi-5465152.html|publisher=[[Daily Bhaskar]]|date=23 November 2016|language=Hindi}}</ref> He has been honored as a 2011 [[Young Global Leaders|Young Global Leader]] by the [[World Economic Forum]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sanjay Chandra,11 other Indians among WEF Young Global Leaders|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/144514/sanjay-chandra11-indians-among-wef.html|publisher=[[Deccan Herald]]|date=9 March 2011|location=Geneva}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=12 Indians among WEF's Young Global Leaders|url=http://www.rediff.com/business/slide-show/slide-show-1-twelve-indians-among-wef-young-global-leaders/20110314.htm#13|publisher=[[rediff.com]]|date=14 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=World Economic Forum names Bhavin Turakhia 'Young Global Leader 2011'|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/press-releases/world-economic-forum-names-bhavin-turakhia-young-global-leader-2011-111031800125_1.html|publisher=[[Business Standard]]|date=18 March 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nBorn in [[Bombay]] in middle class [[Jain]] family, he did his schooling from [[Arya Vidya Mandir]], [[Bandra]].<ref name=\"Forbes\"/> He attended [[D.G. Ruparel College]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nair|first1=Sulekha|title=Never give up, take risks, hire best talent: Business lessons from Bhavin Turakhia|url=http://www.firstpost.com/business/never-give-up-take-risks-hire-best-talent-business-lessons-from-bhavin-turakhia-2997564.html|publisher=[[Firstpost]]|date=12 September 2016}}</ref> to study science and later dropped out<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dropoutdudes.com/success-story-of-two-dropout-brothers-bhavin-turakhia-and-divyank-turakhia/|title=Success Story of Two Dropout Brothers who founded 11 Top Companies of India - Bhavin and Divyank Turakhia|date=2017-12-04|work=Dropout Dudes|access-date=2017-12-05|language=en-US}}</ref> and then completed his bachelor's degree in commerce from [[Sydenham College of Commerce and Economics]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kurian|first1=Boby|last2=Sharma|first2=Samidha|title=Brothers born and bred in city sell e-firm for $900m|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31804&articlexml=Brothers-born-and-bred-in-city-sell-e-23082016001057|publisher=[[The Times of India]]|date=23 August 2016|location=Mumbai}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=India's Internet billionaires|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1160912/jsp/you/story_107607.jsp|publisher=[[Telegraph India]]|date=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1998 with a capital of \u20b925,000<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanherald.fjfhcbxbc.com/content/587154/strength-start-ups.html|title=The strength of start-ups|last1=Bose|first1=Hiren|date=18 December 2016|publisher=[[Deccan Herald]]}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>[http://money.bhaskar.com/news/MON-INDU-STA-these-two-siblings-become-billionaires-after-selling-their-company-business-news-540237.html \u092e\u0941\u0902\u092c\u0908 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u094b \u092d\u093e\u0907\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0928\u0947 25 \u0939\u091c\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0928\u093e\u092f\u093e 9 \u0939\u091c\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c, 16 \u0915\u0940 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u0930 \u092c\u0928\u0947 \u0925\u0947 \u092c\u093f\u200d\u091c\u0928\u0947\u0938\u092e\u0948\u0928...] [[Daily Bhaskar]]. Retrieved 24 August 2016</ref> (US$375), Bhavin Turakhia at the age of 18, started his first tech venture Directi with his brother [[Divyank Turakhia]].<ref name=\"ZeeNews\">{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/business/news/companies/know-how-these-two-mumbai-brothers-turned-rs-25-thousand-into-rs-9000-crores_1922704.html|title=Know how these two Mumbai brothers turned Rs 25 thousand into Rs 9,000 crores|date=26 August 2016|publisher=[[Zee News]]}}</ref><ref name=\"ET\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sabharwal|first1=Punita|title=10 Takes From Bhavin Turakhia On Tech|url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/283186|publisher=[[Entrepreneur (magazine)|Entrepreneur]]|date=2 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=16 \u0938\u093e\u0932 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u0941\u0930\u0941\u0906\u0924, \u0906\u091c 1400 \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u091a\u093e\u0930\u0940 \u0914\u0930 400 \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093f\u092f\u0928 \u0921\u0949\u0932\u0930 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u0902\u092a\u0928\u0940|url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/EDUC-SUST-an-entrepreneur-divyank-turakhia-and-making-a-company-of-400-million-5238560-PHO.html|publisher=[[Daily Bhaskar]]|date=2 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u092a\u093f\u0924\u093e \u0938\u0947 \u0932\u093f\u092f\u093e 25000 \u0915\u093e \u0932\u094b\u0928 \u0914\u0930 \u0905\u092c 9000 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u0902\u092a\u0928\u0940 \u0915\u0947 \u092e\u093e\u0932\u093f\u0915|url=http://naidunia.jagran.com/maharashtra-mumbai-born-siblings-divyank-turakhia-bhavin-turakhia-turn-billionaires-with-sale-of-medianet-804902|publisher=[[Dainik Jagran|Nai Dunia]]|date=26 August 2016|language=Hindi}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Bhavin and Divyank sold four of their web presence companies \u2013 BigRock, [[LogicBoxes]], ResellerClub, and Webhosting.info \u2013 to [[Nasdaq]]-listed U.S.-based web-hosting firm [[Endurance International Group]], for $160 million.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Arora|first1=Varun|title=We will set up family office soon, says Bhavin Turakhia|url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/media-entertainment/2016/08/26/we-will-set-family-office-soon-says-bhavin-turakhia|publisher=[[VCCircle]]|date=26 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Modgil|first1=Shweta|title=It's Our Moral Obligation To Make An Impact Directly Proportional To Our Potential: Bhavin Turakhia, Co-Founder, Directi Group|url=https://inc42.com/startups/interviews/bhavin-turakhia-directi/|accessdate=24 March 2017|publisher=Inc42.com|date=10 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe currently operates [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shaikh|first1=Shadma|title=Bhavin Turakhia invests $25 mn in enterprise messenger Flock for expansion|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/money/bhavin-turakhia-invests-25-mn-in-enterprise-messenger-flock-for-expansion/articleshow/57654006.cms|accessdate=24 March 2017|publisher=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]|date=16 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Arti|title=Bhavin Turakhia to invest $25 mn more in enterprise messenger Flock|url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/technology/2017/03/16/bhavin-turakhia-adds-25-mn-more-enterprise-messenger-flock-expansion?logintype=premium|publisher=[[VCCircle]]|date=16 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=VENTURE DEALS|url=http://fortune.com/2017/03/16/term-sheet-thursday-march-16/|publisher=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]|date=16 March 2016}}</ref> [[Ringo (software)|Ringo]], Radix and [[Zeta India |Zeta]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Personally Tech With Ringo Founder-CEO Bhavin Turakhia|url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/apps/features/personally-tech-with-ringo-founder-ceo-bhavin-turakhia-719339|publisher=[[NDTV]]|date=24 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Mendonca|first1=Jochelle|title=Directi's Bhavin Turakhia to invest $110 million in newer ventures|url=http://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/directis-bhavin-divyank-turakhia-to-invest-110m-to-grow-its-4-new-ventures/54286207|publisher=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]|date=12 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Startup Zeta launches digital LTA solution for employees, Optima Card|url=http://www.firstpost.com/business/startup-zeta-launches-digital-lta-solution-for-employees-optima-card-3198924.html|publisher=[[Firstpost]]|date=11 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Flock 2.0 update brings Teams functionality, deeper app integration|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/scitech/report-flock-20-update-brings-teams-functionality-deeper-app-integration-2253302|publisher=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=8 September 2017|location=[[Mumbai]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Thomas Hector|first1=Dearton|title=Why Bhavin Turakhia thinks Flock 2.0 will be the next big thing in enterprise chat|url=http://techcircle.vccircle.com/2016/09/08/why-bhavin-turakhia-thinks-flock-2-0-will-be-the-next-big-thing-in-enterprise-chat/|publisher=[[VCCircle]]|date=8 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chopra|first1=Ambika|title=Turakhia Brothers To Invest $110 Mn In Four Ventures -- Zeta, Flock, Ringo, & Radix|url=https://inc42.com/buzz/turakhia-brothers-invest-ventures/|accessdate=24 March 2017|publisher=Inc42.com|date=13 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=KJ|first1=Shashidhar|title=Directi's Bhavin Turakhia launches Zeta app to digitize meal vouchers|url=http://www.medianama.com/2016/01/223-directis-bhavin-thurakia-launches-zeta-app-to-digitize-meal-vouchers/|publisher=[[Media Nama]]|date=8 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Directi to hire over 1,000 people|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/directi-to-hire-over-1-000-people-116070100684_1.html|publisher=[[Business Standard]]|date=1 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0907\u0928 \u092d\u093e\u0907\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0928\u0947 \u091a\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0947\u091a\u0940 6000 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u0902\u092a\u0928\u0940, 18 \u0938\u093e\u0932 \u0915\u0940 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092c\u0928\u0947 \u0905\u0930\u092c\u092a\u0924\u093f|url=http://hindi.news18.com/photogallery/bhavin-turakhia-and-divyank-turakhia-brothers-company-acquired-by-chinese-consortium-for-900m-in-cash-912901.html|publisher=[[News18 India]]|date=28 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bhavin Turakhia now bets on Zeta|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31804&articlexml=Bhavin-Turakhia-now-bets-on-Zeta-30092016026023|publisher=[[The Times of India]]|date=30 September 2016|location=Bengaluru}}</ref><ref name=\"THBL\">{{cite news|last1=Kurup|first1=Rajeesh|title=The Turakhia brothers are now worth $1.4 billion|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/info-tech/the-turakhia-brothers-are-now-worth-14-billion/article9022424.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu Business Line]]|date=23 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"AsianAge\"/>\n\t\nIn July 2019, his fintech venture [[Zeta India |Zeta]] received an investment from [[Sodexo]] at a valuation of $300 million. <ref>https://techcrunch.com/2019/07/23/zeta-300m-sodexo/</ref><ref>https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/fintech-platform-zeta-valued-at-300-mn-in-its-series-c-round-led-by-sodexo-1563900056601.html</ref>\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\n* Ranked #95, with a net worth of US$1.3 billion, on the [[Forbes list of Indian billionaires|''Forbes'' list]] of India's 100 Richest People (2016).<ref name=\"Forbes\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sunkara|first1=Keshav|title=Patanjali's Balkrishna, Turakhia brothers enter Forbes rich list; Flipkart founders exit|url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/finance/2016/09/22/patanjali-s-balkrishna-turakhia-brothers-enter-forbes-rich-list-flipkart|publisher=[[VCCircle]]|date=22 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Karmali|first1=Naazneen|title=As India's Richest Make Big Gains, The Entry Price To The Top 100 Touches $1.25 Billion|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/naazneenkarmali/2016/09/21/as-indias-richest-make-big-gains-the-entry-price-to-the-top-100-touches-1-25-billion/#27e143363f81|newspaper=[[Forbes India]]|date=21 September 2016}}</ref>\n* Serial Entrepreneur of the Year and Entrepreneur of the Year in Innovation and Technology by [[Entrepreneur (magazine)]], India (2016).<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jain|first1=Samiksha|title=Here Are The Winners Of The Prestigious 6th Annual Entrepreneur India Awards 2016|url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/281909|publisher=[[Entrepreneur (magazine)|Entrepreneur]]|date=5 September 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"THBL\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Bhosale|first1=Akshay|title=\u2018Serial Entrepreneur\u2019 Bhavin Turakhia Bags Dual Awards At Annual Entrepreneur India Awards 2016!|url=http://digitalconqurer.com/news/serial-entrepreneur-bhavin-turakhia-bags-dual-awards-annual-entrepreneur-india-awards-2016/|publisher=DigitalConqurer|date=25 August 2016}}</ref>\n* The ETPanache Trendsetter Award by [[The Economic Times]] (2016).<ref>{{cite news|title=ETPanache Trendsetter Awards 2016: Ananya Birla, Dipa Karmakar, Karan Johar emerge winners|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/etpanache-trendsetter-awards-2016-ananya-birla-dipa-karmakar-karan-johar-emerge-winners/articleshow/54708195.cms|publisher=[[The Economic Times]]|date=18 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|tit