5-en.pdf|publisher=Icann.org|date=12 July 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=New|first1=William|title=ICANN's Process For Strategic Plan, .Net Domain Renewal Questioned|url=https://www.ip-watch.org/2005/07/13/icanns-process-for-strategic-plan-net-domain-renewal-questioned/|publisher=Ip-watch.org|date=13 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{portal|Biography|India}}\n* [[List of Indian entrepreneurs]]\n* [[List of Internet entrepreneurs]]\n* [[Information Technology Act, 2000]]\n* [[Legal aspects of computing]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://bhavin.directi.com/about-me/ Official website]\n* [https://www.forbes.com/profile/bhavin-divyank-turakhia/ Bhavin & Divyank Turakhia] at [[Forbes]]\n* [http://bwdisrupt.businessworld.in/article/-Focus-on-Creating-Value-Rather-than-Profitability-To-Do-Well-in-the-Long-Run-Bhavin-Turakhia/26-12-2016-110278/ Bhavin Turakhia's Interview] at [[Businessworld]]\n* [http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/et-now/daily/how-turakhia-duo-spends-the-moolah/videoshow/54751279.cms How Turakhia duo spends the moolah!] at [[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Turakhia, Bhavin}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Gujarati people]]\n[[Category:Indian billionaires]]\n[[Category:Indian chief executives]]\n[[Category:Indian industrialists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Mumbai alumni]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Mumbai]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Bhavin Turakhia\n| image = Bhavin Turakhia.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Bhavin Turakhia\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1979|12|21|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Bombay]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| nationality = \n| alma_mater = Arya Vidya Mandir<br>[[D. G. Ruparel College of Arts, Science and Commerce]]<br>[[Sydenham College of Commerce and Economics]]\n| occupation = {{unbulleted list| CEO & founder of Directi, [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]], Radix and [[Ringo (software)|Ringo]] | Co-founder of Zeta }}\n| known_for   = Directi, Radix, [[Ringo (software)|Ringo]], [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]], [[Zeta India|Zeta]], and [[CodeChef]]\n| website = \n| footnotes = \n| networth = {{increase}}[[United States dollar|US$]]1.3 [[1,000,000,000 (number)|billion]] (2016)<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/profile/bhavin-divyank-turakhia/ Bhavin Turakhia Profile]. [[Forbes.com]]. Retrieved 9 October 2016.</ref>\n| relations = \n}}\n\n'''Bhavin Turakhia''' (born 21 December 1979)  is an Indian billionaire <ref>{{cite news |title=Family matters: Bhavin Turakhia credits his father, humble beginnings for success |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/family-matters-bhavin-turakhia-credits-his-father-humble-beginnings-for-success/articleshow/72341438.cms |publisher=The Economic Times |date=Dec 3, 2019}}</ref> and serial entrepreneur<ref>{{cite news |title=Video I followed my father's advice and became a billionaire |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/av/business-50268357/i-followed-my-father-s-advice-and-became-a-billionaire |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=6 November 2019}}</ref>, and the founder of [[Flock (messaging service)|Flock]], Radix, [[CodeChef]] and [[Zeta India|Zeta]]. He is the CEO of Flock and Zeta.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bhavin Turakhia to invest $25 mn in Flock, an enterprise team messenger|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/bhavin-turakhia-to-invest-25-mn-in-flock-an-enterprise-team-messenger/article9587411.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu Business Line]]|date=15 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"AsianAge\">{{cite news|last1=Banerjee|first1=Sudeshna|title=The winner takes it all|url=http://www.asianage.com/people/winner-takes-it-all-181|publisher=[[Asian Age]]|date=4 November 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ET\">{{cite news|last1=Mendonca|first1=Jochelle|title=Directi, founded by brothers Bhavin and Divyank Turakhia, to buy 1 lakh sq feet building|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/directi-founded-by-brothers-bhavin-and-divyank-turakhia-to-buy-1-lakh-sq-feet-building/articleshow/54287458.cms|publisher=[[The Economic Times|Economic Times]]|date=19 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0926\u094b \u092d\u093e\u0907\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u0902\u092a\u0928\u0940, 25000 \u0938\u0947 \u0936\u0941\u0930\u0941 \u0915\u0940 \u0914\u0930 6000 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091a\u0940\u0928 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0947\u091a \u0926\u0940|url=http://www.livehindustan.com/news/business/article1-divyank-turakhia-sold-medianet-for-chinese-company--554287.html|publisher=Live Hindutan|date=27 August 2017|location=New Delhi|language=Hindi}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=These Stories Of Overnight Success Defy Logic|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/12/29/these-stories-of-overnight-success-defy-logic/|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|date=2 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=John|first1=Jesus|title=Making life less taxing for staff and employers|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/specials/emerging-entrepreneurs/making-life-less-taxing-for-staff-and-employers/article8897928.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu Business Line]]|date=25 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Das|first1=Poulomi|title=This Indian tech company has one of the most fun hiring processes ever|url=http://www.businessinsider.in/This-Indian-tech-company-has-one-of-the-most-fun-hiring-processes-ever/articleshow/53544416.cms|publisher=[[Business Insider]]|date=4 August 2016}}</ref> In 2016, Bhavin was ranked as the 95th richest person in India, with a net worth of US$1.3 billion, along with his brother [[Divyank Turakhia]], according to ''[[Forbes]]''.<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news|last1=Raghunathan|first1=Anuradha|title=Meet the technology whiz kids Bhavin and Divyank Turakhia|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/india-rich-list-2016/meet-the-technology-whiz-kids-bhavin-and-divyank-turakhia/44959/1|newspaper=[[Forbes India]