ake risks, hire best talent: Business lessons from Bhavin Turakhia|url=http://www.firstpost.com/business/never-give-up-take-risks-hire-best-talent-business-lessons-from-bhavin-turakhia-2997564.html|publisher=[[Firstpost]]|date=12 September 2016}}</ref> to study science and later dropped out<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dropoutdudes.com/success-story-of-two-dropout-brothers-bhavin-turakhia-and-divyank-turakhia/|title=Success Story of Two Dropout Brothers who founded 11 Top Companies of India - Bhavin and Divyank Turakhia|date=2017-12-04|work=Dropout Dudes|access-date=2017-12-05|language=en-US}}</ref> and then completed his bachelor's degree in commerce from [[Sydenham College of Commerce and Economics]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kurian|first1=Boby|last2=Sharma|first2=Samidha|title=Brothers born and bred in city sell e-firm for $900m|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31804&articlexml=Brothers-born-and-bred-in-city-sell-e-23082016001057|publisher=[[The Times of India]]|date=23 August 2016|location=Mumbai}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=India's Internet billionaires|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1160912/jsp/you/story_107607.jsp|publisher=[[Telegraph India]]|date=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1998 with a capital of \u20b925,000<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanherald.fjfhcbxbc.com/content/587154/strength-start-ups.html|title=The strength of start-ups|last1=Bose|first1=Hiren|date=18 December 2016|publisher=[[Deccan Herald]]}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>[http://money.bhaskar.com/news/MON-INDU-STA-these-two-siblings-become-billionaires-after-selling-their-company-business-news-540237.html \u092e\u0941\u0902\u092c\u0908 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u094b \u092d\u093e\u0907\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0928\u0947 25 \u0939\u091c\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u094b \u092c\u0928\u093e\u092f\u093e 9 \u0939\u091c\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u0930\u094b\u0921\u093c, 16 \u0915\u0940 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u0930 \u092c\u0928\u