{"title_page": "Heo Hoon", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Heo Hoon\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| position  = [[Point guard]] \n| height_ft = 5\n| height_in = 11\n| weight_lb = \n| league = [[Korean Basketball League]]\n| team   = [[Busan KT Sonicboom]]\n| number = 2\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1995|8|16}}\n| birth_place = [[Seoul, South Korea]]\n| nationality = [[South Korea]]n\n| high_school =\n| college = \n| draft_year = 2017\n| career_start = 2017\n| career_end = \n| years1 =2017-present\n| team1  = [[Busan KT Sonicboom]]\n| years2 = \n| team2  = \n| years3 = \n| team3  = \n| years4 = \n| team4  = \n| years5 = \n| team5  = \n| years6 = \n| team6  = \n| years7 = \n| team7  = \n| highlights   = \n|medaltemplates= \n}}\n\n'''Heo Hoon''' (born 16 August 1995) is a South Korean professional [[basketball]] player.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/basketballworldcup/2019/player/Hoon-Heo|title=Hoon HEO at the FIBA Basketball World Cup 2019|website=FIBA.basketball}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2019-08-01/South-Korea-confirms-final-roster-for-FIBA-Basketball-World-Cup-IO3i0TN3Co/index.html|title=South Korea confirms final roster for FIBA Basketball World Cup|website=news.cgtn.com}}</ref> He plays for the [[Korean Basketball League|South Korean side]] [[Busan KT Sonicboom]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://basketball.asia-basket.com/player/Hoon-Heo/South-Korea/KT-Sonicboom/231568|title=Hoon Heo Basketball Player Profile, KT Sonicboom, News, KBL stats, Career, Games Logs, Best, Awards - asia-basket|website=Eurobasket LLC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://basketball.eurobasket.com/player/Hoon-Heo/South-Korea/KT-Sonicboom/231568|title=Hoon Heo Basketball Player Profile, KT Sonicboom, News, KBL stats, Career, Games Logs, Best, Awards - eurobasket|website=Eurobasket LLC}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nHoon joined the [[Busan KT Sonicboom]] in 2017, he voted to be a Korean Basketball league All star in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3071974|title=Heo Hoon makes sibling history with All-Star fan vote win-INSIDE Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\n==National team==\n===Junior teams===\nHoon represented Korea in the [[2012 FIBA Under-17 World Championship]], where he averaged 17.7 points, 2 rebounds and 2.9 assists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.proballers.com/basketball/team/2686/u17-korea/2012|title=U17 Korea Roster, Schedule, Stats|website=Proballers}}</ref> \nHoon also participated in the [[2013 FIBA Under-19 World Championship]], where he averaged 12.8 points, 3.4 rebounds and 3.2 assists<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.proballers.com/basketball/team/2698/u19-korea/2013|title=U19 Korea Roster, Schedule, Stats|website=Proballers}}</ref>\n\n===Senior team===\nHoon participated in the qualifiers to the 2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup in China, he averaged 6.7 points, 0.5 rebounds and 1.5 assists<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/basketball/heo-hoon/315347/|title=Heo Hoon - Basketball player profile & career statistics - Global Sports Archive|website=globalsportsarchive.com}}</ref>\nHoon represents the South Korean national basketball team, He represented the team at [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup]] where he averaged 4.2 points, 0.4 rebounds and 0.8 assist at the tournament.<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/international/players/hoon-heo-1.html|title=Hoon Heo International Stats|website=Basketball-Reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHoon's older brother ''Heo Ung'' is a professional basketball player for the [[Wonju DB Promy]]. His father ''Hur Jae'' is a former headcoach of the South Korean National Basketball team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mengnews.joins.com/view.aspx?aid=3059591|title=Heo bros hit the court for fraternal face-off-INSIDE Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{improve categories|date=January 2020}}\n\n[[Category:2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup players]]\n[[Category:South Korean men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Heo Hoon\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| position  = [[Point guard]] \n| height_ft = 5\n| height_in = 11\n| weight_lb = \n| league = [[Korean Basketball League]]\n| team   = [[Busan KT Sonicboom]]\n| number = 2\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1995|8|16}}\n| birth_place = [[Seoul, South Korea]]\n| nationality = [[South Korea]]n\n| high_school =\n| college = \n| draft_year = 2017\n| career_start = 2017\n| career_end = \n| years1 =2017-present\n| team1  = [[Busan KT Sonicboom]]\n| years2 = \n| team2  = \n| years3 = \n| team3  = \n| years4 = \n| team4  = \n| years5 = \n| team5  = \n| years6 = \n| team6  = \n| years7 = \n| team7  = \n| highlights   = \n|medaltemplates= \n}}\n\n'''Heo Hoon''' (born 16 August 1995) is a South Korean professional [[basketball]] player.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/basketballworldcup/2019/player/Hoon-Heo|title=Hoon HEO at the FIBA Basketball World Cup 2019|website=FIBA.basketball}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2019-08-01/South-Korea-confirms-final-roster-for-FIBA-Basketball-World-Cup-IO3i0TN3Co/index.html|title=South Korea confirms final roster for FIBA Basketball World Cup|website=news.cgtn.com}}</ref> He plays for the [[Korean Basketball League|South Korean side]] [[Busan KT Sonicboom]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://basketball.asia-basket.com/player/Hoon-Heo/South-Korea/KT-Sonicboom/231568|title=Hoon Heo Basketball Player Profile, KT Sonicboom, News, KBL stats, Career, Games Logs, Best, Awards - asia-basket|website=Eurobasket LLC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://basketball.eurobasket.com/