y]]. His father ''Hur Jae'' is a former headcoach of the South Korean National Basketball team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mengnews.joins.com/view.aspx?aid=3059591|title=Heo bros hit the court for fraternal face-off-INSIDE Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{improve categories|date=January 2020}}\n\n[[Category:2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup players]]\n[[Category:South Korean men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Shonebrooks", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eClub career:spelling basketballWP:TYPO", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heo_Hoon"}
{"title_page": "UCI World Ranking", "text_new": "For the 2016 season the '''[[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]]''' revamped the points system used to rank men's [[road cycling]] riders. The following table summarises the new rankings, how points are scored towards them and how points are scaled. \n\n==UCI World Ranking (men)==\n===Current rankings===\n{{See also|2019 UCI World Tour|2019 UCI Africa Tour|2019 UCI America Tour|2019 UCI Asia Tour|2019 UCI Europe Tour|2019 UCI Oceania Tour}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break|width=60%}}\n{{Current Top 10 Men's Road Rankings - Individual}}\n{{col-break|width=40%}}\n{{Current Top 10 Men's Road Rankings - Nations}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Number one ranked riders and nations===\n{{Number one ranked riders and nations}}\n\n===Year-end UCI World Rankings===\n\nThe following is a list of Top 3 riders and nations at the end of each season:<ref>http://www.uci.org/road/rankings</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|+ Individual Ranking\n|-\n!Year\n!colspan=2| 1st\n!colspan=2| 2nd\n!colspan=2| 3rd\n|-\n| [[2019 UCI World Ranking|2019]]\n| align=left|{{Flagathlete|[[Primo\u017e Rogli\u010d]]|SLO}} [[Team Jumbo\u2013Visma]]\n| 4705.28 pts\n| align=left|{{Flagathlete|[[Julian Alaphilippe]]|FRA}}\n[[Team Jumbo\u2013Visma]]\n| 3569.95 pts\n| align=left|{{Flagathlete|[[Jakob Fuglsang]]|DEN}}\n[[Astana Pro Team]]\n|3472.5 pts\n|-\n| [[2018 UCI World Ranking|2018]]\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Alejandro Valverde]]|ESP}}{{ct|MOV|2018}}\n| 4168 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Simon Yates (cyclist)|Simon Yates]] <br> {{ct|ORS|2018}} || 3160 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Elia Viviani]] <br> {{ct|QST|2018}} ||3106 pts\n|-\n| [[2017 UCI World Ranking|2017]]\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Greg Van Avermaet]]|BEL}} <br> {{ct|BMC|2017}} || 4148 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Chris Froome]] <br> {{ct|SKY|2017}} || 3692 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Peter Sagan]] <br> {{ct|BOH|2017}} || 3344 pts\n|-\n| [[2016 UCI World Ranking|