 pts\n| align=left| {{FRA}} || 12123 pts\n|-\n|[[2018 UCI World Ranking|2018]]\n| align=left| {{BEL}} || 14502.02 pts\n| align=left| {{FRA}} || 13628.12 pts\n| align=left| {{ITA}} || 12142.76 pts\n|}\n\n==UCI World Ranking (women)==\n===Current rankings===\n{{See also|2019 UCI Women's World Tour}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break|width=60%}}\n{{Current top 5 Women's UCI Rankings - Individuals}}\n{{col-end}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break|width=50%}}\n{{Current top 5 Women's UCI Rankings - Teams}}\n{{col-break|width=50%}}\n{{Current top 5 Women's UCI Rankings - Nations}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Number one ranked riders and nations===\n{{Number one ranked riders, teams & nations (women)}}\n\n==Ranking system==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Ranking !! Summary\n|-\n| Individual UCI World Ranking || This ranking system is calculated on a 52 week rolling basis, rankings are updated each Monday. The ranking at the end of the calendar year will be utilised to award an annual winner. Unlike previous ranking systems the UCI World Classification will include <u>all</u> male riders from the World Tour down to U23 riders. Points will be awarded on all races from World Tour level down to 1.2 and 2.2 races.\n|-\n| UCI World Ranking by nations || This is based on the world ranking with the best eight riders from each country contributing towards their nation's overall score.\n|-\n|UCI WorldTour Rankings || This is the UCI WorldTour ranking of riders, teams and nations taking part in the events of the UCI WorldTour. Only riders being part of a UCI WorldTeam obtain points in UCI WorldTour races.\n|-\n| Continental Ranking || There will be subsets of rankings which are made up from points scored in non-World Tour races (i.e, UCI Europe Tour, UCI Asia Tour etc) for individuals, teams and nations. This will therefore allow one rider to appear in more than one ranking, for example a rider who won Strade Bianchi and a stage in the Tour of California would be part of the Europe Tour and America Tour rankings.\n|-\n|}\n\n===Previous and current ranking systems===\n<center><timeline>\nImageSize = width:1200 height:300\nPlotArea  = top:10 bottom:80 right:20 left:20\nLegend    = columns:4 left:30 top:58 columnwidth:270\n\nAlignBars  = early\nDateFormat = dd/mm/yyyy\nPeriod     = from:01/01/1945 till:31/12/2030\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nScaleMinor = grid:black unit:year increment:5 start:01/01/1945\n\nColors =\n  id:canvas value:gray(0.95)\n  id:1     value:rgb(1,0,0) legend:Challenge_Desgrange-Colombo_(1948\u20131958)\n  id:2     value:rgb(1,0.3,0) legend:Super_Prestige_Pernod_International_(1958\u20131988)\n  id:3     value:rgb(1,0.5,0) legend:UCI_Road_World_Rankings_(1984\u20132004)\n  id:4     value:rgb(1,0.8,0) legend:UCI_Road_World_Cup_(1989\u20132004)\n  id:5     value:rgb(1,0.9,0) legend:UCI_ProTour_(2005\u20132010)\n  id:6     value:rgb(0.5,1,0.2) legend:UCI_Africa_Tour_(2005\u2013_Present)\n  id:7     value:rgb(0.45,1,0) legend:UCI_America_Tour_(2005\u2013_Present)\n  id:8     value:rgb(0,1,0) legend:UCI_Asia_Tour_(2005\u2013_Present)\n  id:9     value:rgb(0.2,0.8,0.2) legend:UCI_Europe_Tour_(2005\u2013_Present)\n  id:10     value:rgb(0,0.5,0) legend:UCI_Oceania_Tour_(2005\u2013_Present)\n  id:11     value:rgb(0,0.8,1) legend:UCI_World_Tour_(2009\u2013_2018)\n  id:12    value:rgb(0,0,1) legend:UCI_World_Rankings_(2016\u2013_Present)\n\nBackgroundcolors = canvas:canvas\n\nBarData =\n  barset:Hurricane\n  bar:Month\n\nPlotData=\n  barset:Hurricane width:11 align:left fontsize:M shift:(4,-4) anchor:till\n  from:01/01/1948 till:01/01/1958 color:1 text:[[Challenge Desgrange-Colombo]]\n  from:01/01/1958 till:31/12/1988 color:2 text:[[Super_Prestige_Pernod_International]]\n  from:01/01/1984 till:31/12/2004 color:3 text:[[UCI Road World Rankings]]\n  from:01/01/1989 till:31/12/2004 color:4 text:[[UCI Road World Cup]]\n  from:01/01/2005 till:31/12/2010 color:5 text:[[UCI ProTour]]\n  from:01/01/2005 till:31/12/2019 color:6 text:[[UCI Africa Tour]]\n  fro