owspan=3|5 \n|-\n| 14 || 50 || 20 || 15 || 25\n|-\n| 15 || 40 || 15 || 10 || 20\n|-\n| 16 || 35 || 10 || rowspan=15|5  || rowspan=5| 3 || 15 || rowspan=5| 3 ||style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=24|\n|-\n| 17 || rowspan=5|30 || rowspan=4|5 || 10\n|-\n| 18 || rowspan=13|5\n|-\n| 19 \n|-\n| 20 \n|-\n| 21 || style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=19| || style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=19| ||style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=19|\n|-\n| 22 || rowspan=10|20\n|-\n| 23 \n|-\n| 24 \n|-\n| 25 \n|-\n| 26 \n|-\n| 27 \n|-\n| 28 \n|-\n| 29 \n|-\n| 30 \n|-\n| 31 || rowspan=6|3 || rowspan=5|3\n|-\n| 32 || rowspan=6|10\n|-\n| 33 \n|-\n| 34 \n|-\n| 35 \n|-\n| 36\u201340 || 1\n|-\n| 41\u201350 || style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=3| || style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=3|\n|-\n| 51\u201355 || 5\n|-\n| 56\u201360 || 3\n|}\n\n====Team Time Trial Championships====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Relative Position !! World Championships !! Continental Championships\n|-\n|  1 || 500 || 70\n|-\n|  2 || 400 || 55\n|-\n|  3 || 325 || 40\n|-\n|  4 || 275 || 30\n|-\n|  5 || 225 || 25\n|-\n|  6 || 175 || 20\n|-\n|  7 || 150 || 15\n|-\n|  8 || 125 || 10\n|-\n|  9 || 100 || 5\n|-\n|  10 || 85 || 3\n|-\n|  11 || 70 || style=\"background:lightgrey;\" rowspan=5|\n|-\n|  12 || 60\n|-\n|  13\u201315 || 50\n|-\n|  16\u201320 || 30\n|-\n|  21\u201325 || 25\n|}\nSource:<ref>{{cite web |title=UCI CYCLING REGULATIONS - PART 2 ROAD RACES |url=http://www.uci.org/docs/default-source/rules-and-regulations/part-ii---road-races.pdf?sfvrsn=448068eb_10 |website=UCI.org |accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.uci.org/docs/default-source/rules-and-regulations/part-ii---road-races.pdf?sfvrsn=448068eb_10 Official UCI Rules]\n\n{{Road bicycle racing season-long competitions}}\n{{Road bicycle racing}}\n{{UCI World Tour Winners}}\n{{UCI Women's Road Rankings}}\n{{Sport world rankings}}\n\n[[Category:UCI tours|Ranking]]\n[[Category:Men's road cycling]]\n[[Category:Sports world rankings]]\n[[Category:Cycling records and statistics]]\n", "text_old": "For the 2016 season the '''[[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]]''' revamped the points system used to rank men's [[road cycling]] riders. The following table summarises the new rankings, how points are scored towards them and how points are scaled. \n\n==UCI World Ranking (men)==\n===Current rankings===\n{{See also|2019 UCI World Tour|2019 UCI Africa Tour|2019 UCI America Tour|2019 UCI Asia Tour|2019 UCI Europe Tour|2019 UCI Oceania Tour}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break|width=60%}}\n{{Current Top 10 Men's Road Rankings - Individual}}\n{{col-break|width=40%}}\n{{Current Top 10 Men's Road Rankings - Nations}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Number one ranked riders and nations===\n{{Number one ranked riders and nations}}\n\n===Year-end UCI World Rankings===\n\nThe following is a list of Top 3 riders and nations at the end of each season:<ref>http://www.uci.org/road/rankings</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|+ Individual Ranking\n|-\n!Year\n!colspan=2| 1st\n!colspan=2| 2nd\n!colspan=2| 3rd\n|-\n| [[2019 UCI World Ranking|2019]]\n| align=left|{{Flagathlete|[[Primo\u017e Rogli\u010d]]|SLO}}\n[[Team Jumbo\u2013Visma]]\n| 4705.28 pts\n| align=left|{{Flagathlete|[[Julian Alaphilippe]]|FRA}}\n[[Team Jumbo\u2013Visma]]\n| 3569.95 pts\n| align=left|{{Flagathlete|[[Jakob Fuglsang]]|DEN}}\n[[Astana Pro Team]]\n|3472.5 pts\n|-\n| [[2018 UCI World Ranking|2018]]\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Alejandro Valverde]]|ESP}}{{ct|MOV|2018}}\n| 4168 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Simon Yates (cyclist)|Simon Yates]] <br> {{ct|ORS|2018}} || 3160 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Elia Viviani]] <br> {{ct|QST|2018}} ||3106 pts\n|-\n| [[2017 UCI World Ranking|2017]]\n| align=left| {{flagathlete|[[Greg Van Avermaet]]|BEL}} <br> {{ct|BMC|2017}} || 4148 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Chris Froome]] <br> {{ct|SKY|2017}} || 3692 pts\n| align=left| {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Peter Saga